ed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Maud de Argentine was born in 1239, in Mentmore, Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, William d' Argentine, was 50 and her mother, Mrs. William d' Argentine, was 148. She had at least 2 sons with Roger de Stratele."},"et":{"1239–":"1239–Surnud","1114–Male":"1114–Surnud","1239–Female":"1239–Surnud","1235–1276":"1235–1276","1262–1281":"1262–1281","1264–1316":"1264–1316","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1092–Female":"1092–Surnud","1239":"1239","1190":"1190","1316":"1316","1235":"1235","1114":"1114","1276":"1276","1264":"1264","abt 1262":"umbes 1262","1262":"1262","abt 1264":"umbes 1264","1281":"1281","1092":"1092","Mentmore, Buckingham, England, Great Britain":"Mentmore, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of Mentmore, Bckngh, Engl":"Mentmore, Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1239–":"1239–Kuollut","1114–Male":"1114–Kuollut","1239–Female":"1239–Kuollut","1235–1276":"1235–1276","1262–1281":"1262–1281","1264–1316":"1264–1316","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1092–Female":"1092–Kuollut","1239":"1239","1190":"1190","1316":"1316","1235":"1235","1114":"1114","1276":"1276","1264":"1264","abt 1262":"noin 1262","1262":"1262","abt 1264":"noin 1264","1281":"1281","1092":"1092","Mentmore, Buckingham, England, Great Britain":"Mentmore, Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Mentmore, Bckngh, Engl":"Mentmore, Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1239–":"1239–Décédée","1114–Male":"1114–Décédé","1239–Female":"1239–Décédée","1235–1276":"1235–1276","1262